'''''Windwalker''''' is a 1989 video game published by [[Origin Systems]].

==Gameplay==
''Windwalker'' is a game in which the player uses martial arts while seeking enlightenment, in the sequel to ''[[Moebius: The Orb of Celestial Harmony]]''.<ref name="CGW69"/>

==Reception==
Dennis Owens reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "''Windwalker'' is an excellent game for fans of ''Moebius'' and for anyone looking for a combination action/role-playing game with an Oriental flair and a gentleness of spirit."<ref name="CGW69">{{cite magazine |last=Owens |first=Dennis |title="Peace, Young One . . .": Origin's "Windwalker" |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=March 1990 |volume=1 |issue=69 |pages=27}}</ref>

